         <td align="left" colspan="5">
          <p>
           <img width="129" hspace="8" height="172" border="1" align="left" alt="" src="images/happenings/devorrisNancy.jpg" />
           The Southern Alleghenies Museum of Art hosted its third annual Night of Distinction on April 26, 2014.
          </p>
          <p>
           For the first time, the event was held at SAMA's Altoona facility as the museum celebrates its 35th anniversary in Blair County. SAMA also honored four individuals at the program, each of whom has strong ties to the Altoona community.
          </p>
          <p>
           Night of Distinction was established as a platform to honor some of the museum's most dedicated and longest-serving benefactors. This year, SAMA presented Dr. Betty J. Lowell Cottle and
           <strong>
            Nancy Devorris
           </strong>
           with Service to the Arts awards, while Joseph Mack and Gerald P. Wolf were honored with Trustee Emeritus appointments.
          </p>
          <p>
           <a class="bodylink" target="_blank" href="http://www.altoonamirror.com/page/content.detail/id/582446/SAMA-Night-of-Distinction-honors-Altoona-site--patrons.html?nav=738">
            Congratulations to Nancy, read more here in the Altoona Mirror.
           </a>
