         <td height="45">
         </td>
         <td valign="top" align="left" colspan="6">
          <strong>
           Condolences to the family of Bernie Covitch.
          </strong>
          Bernard, 96, of Ebensburg, passed away Thursday, September 13, 2012. He graduated from Ebensburg-Cambria High School in 1934 and earned a bachelor's degree at Penn State University, where he played violin in the symphony and, more importantly, wooed his sweetheart, Ruthie. The two married in 1943 while he served as a captain in the U.S. Army, and they shared a lifetime of love for travel, fine dining and even finer friends and family. He was an avid runner, a hobby he started in his 60s.
          <a class="bodylink" target="_blank" href="http://www.altoonamirror.com/page/content.detail/id/564193/Bernard-Covitch.html?nav=743">
           Read the complete obituary here.
          </a>
         </td>
        </tr>
