           <img width="129" hspace="8" height="172" border="1" align="left" alt="" src="images/obits/wayneJerry.jpg" />
           <strong>
            Condolences to the family of Jerry Wayne.
           </strong>
           Jerry, 82, Altoona, died early Wednesday morning, June 14, 2012, at Hahnemann Medical Center, Philadelphia, after a brief illness.
          </p>
          <p>
           He was born in Latrobe, son of the late Morris and Ella (Goldman) Wayne. He married Janet Rosenberg in 1968.
          </p>
          <p>
           Surviving are his wife; his loving children: Tina Berman and husband, Robert, of Haddonfield, N.J., and David and wife, Jessica, of Chicago; and four grandchildren: Ella, Charlotte, Natalie and Harrison, who were his pride and joy and to whom he was known as "Poppy."
          </p>
          <p>
           Jerry was a graduate of Altoona High School and earned a Bachelor of Science degree from Penn State University after his service with the U.S. Army. He had a partnership with his father in the Altoona Glassware Supply Co. Together with his wife, they opened the Taylor Rental Center, later renamed The Rental Center, selling the business and retiring in 2001.
           <a class="bodylink" target="_blank" href="http://www.altoonamirror.com/page/content.detail/id/561660/Jerome-Hillis--Jerry--Wayne.html?nav=743">
            Read the complete obituary here.
